place_info.title: The Gallery Cafe
place_info.address: Kalakriti Art Complex, 8-2-465, Road No 4, Green Valley, Banjara Hills, Hyderabad, Telangana 500034, India

reviews.snippet:
If you are looking for a place to spend an afternoon chatting with a friend over good vegetarian food, this is the perfect place. The service is prompt but discrete, there is no distracting music and the place is relatively uncrowded so nobody rushes at you with the bill even before you finish. There are limited vegan options, but the entire menu is vegetarian so you have a lot to choose from. They are also good with minor customisations. Both the dishes we ordered were a little on the spicy side, so if you have spice intolerance, do ask them to tone it down a bit- I found it prefect. The beautiful art work on the walls adds to the ambiance without detracting from the meal. Will certainly revisit.
There is ample parking inside, which is an added bonus. We took the stairs, but there is also a lift. You can also drop in at the Art Gallery on the way in or out- there is always some interesting exhibition going on there.

reviews.snippet:
Recently, we visited The Gallery Cafe ,  located in Banjara Hills. First impressions - it's a decent spot , particularly for art lovers who might enjoy the artistic ambience.

Now, coming to the food, we tried a variety of items: White Sauce Penne Veg Pasta, French Fries, Vietnamese Iced Coffee, Brownie Shake, and the Capricorn Pizza. To be honest, except for the pizza, everything was quite disappointing. The Capricorn Pizza was good, though not exceptional. It had a typical taste that you'd find in many Hyderabad cafes—satisfying but nothing extraordinary.

The two most disappointing items were the White Sauce Penne Pasta and the Vietnamese Iced Coffee. The pasta’s sauce was the biggest letdown. The consistency was thin and watery, far from the creamy texture I expected, and the flavor was bland. Additionally, the portion size of the pasta was a bit underwhelming considering the price, which added to the disappointment.

As for the Vietnamese Iced Coffee, it was the most disappointing. We ordered it based on the promising description, which mentioned it as “delightfully sweet, full-bodied, and almost like a dessert.” However, what we received was far from that—it lacked sweetness and tasted more like plain black coffee with ice cubes, completely missing the dessert-like appeal the menu promised.

The French fries were average, but the cheese served alongside lacked flavor and didn’t complement the fries well. The brownie shake was another letdown—it tasted oddly like Cerelac, possibly due to the poor quality of the brownie used, which overpowered the shake’s flavor.

Overall, the food and drinks need considerable improvement. There's a lot of scope for enhancing the taste and ensuring that menu descriptions align with what’s actually served, especially for the coffee options.

reviews.snippet:
There is an amazing art gallery which was nearly about 20 years old. The arts they have exhibited there are really amazing and you can buy them even. There will be some exhibitions going on every month. Other than painting, they even sell historical books, pens, bags, pillows, scarfs, mugs, coaster plates. The range of the painting start from 8K to 80K. They keep changing the painting for every week or 15 days.
The cafe was started just 3 years ago. The taste of the food is normal. Pizzas are not at all advisable to order. The rest all are average.
Food taste is 3.5/5
Ambience is 5/5
Service is 4.5/5
Overall experience is good 4/5.
Please visit the gallery. It's amazing.

reviews.snippet:
This was a random find. We went in not knowing what to expect.

There was easy parking, the place itself is hidden at the end of a long pathway.

The cafe is on the 2nd floor. You pass through a gallery on the ground and some artistic gifts on the first floor.

The food was really good. The staff is super helpful and their recommendations were really good. They recommended some toast with fresh avacado and a custard apple shake with zero added sugar.

I enjoyed every bit of the food. If you happen to visit in December, you must try the shake.

reviews.snippet:
I have been to this place recently and have observed something which I wasn't able to witness for a long time. This cafe is located exactly on top of a Art Gallery which was closed on the day we visited and we haven't found many vehicles parked outside. I was very skeptical on the taste and visited with friends. We ordered Shakes and they didn't have the same so was disappointed and wanted to move to some other cafe. But somehow wanted to try something. We ordered Mojito, Cheese Sticks and Penne Alfredo. The taste was so good that we excused them for the shakes and wanted to order more but we were full down then.

In conclusion, worth the visit. Don't be disappointed if they are not having a few items from menu. Try out their Pasta for sure.

reviews.snippet:
#WhenAtBanjarahills and you are craving for vegetarian continental cafe then The Gallery Cafe can be one of your Saviour.

Owing to the Name, you will see a lot of artistic crafts and scribbled paintings allover with spacious seating that can fit in 75 pax easily. Loved the smokey sambrani that's used to keep the environment relaxed.

A pretty cool and small menu that leaves you no confusion to choose. The pricing for two would be around 500-800INR which is decent enough I think.

Well, it's been quite a while, I had a proper Lasagna (My last and best was at The Pasta Bar Veneto which is closed now) thought I will give it a shot here and ordered #Vegetable #Lasagna. Though the taste was bang on, I would love more parmesan cheese on the top and baked. Missed that little cheesy effect. Moving on and I asked for the best pizza suggestion for which I got, #FunkieVeggieLoverPizza. Cheese and white sauce overloaded pizza that you can not see the toppings and have to call the person asking for toppings 😛 ... Again the taste and toppings were very good but this time the cheese wasn't gooey 😞 ..

I am neither satisfied nor left sad for the fact I have used #zomatogold 😛 . Overbill I paid was only for the lasagna which is 320 including taxes.

Well, Will, I go again? Yes for their cheesecake 😛
#annadathasukhibhava

#ClickEatXploreYo Live #CEXY
